/-
  Normal-form games and the Prisoner's Dilemma.

  A Game consists of:
  - A finite set of players
  - For each player, a finite set of strategies
  - For each strategy profile, a payoff for each player

  Defines: Game, StrategyProfile, payoff, NashEquilibrium.

  Prisoner's Dilemma (Paper §2): the standard payoff ordering is
    T > R > P > S  (Temptation > Reward > Punishment > Sucker).
  (Defect, Defect) is the unique Nash equilibrium of the one-shot PD.
-/
